hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Hydrostatic equilibrium and ideal gas equations:
$$P_c = C_1 G M_c^{2/3}\rho_c^{4/3}$$,
$$P_c = \frac{\rho_c k_B T_c}{\mu m_p}.$$
2. Equate pressures and solve for $\rho_c$:
$$\frac{\rho_c k_B T_c}{\mu m_p}=C_1 G M_c^{2/3}\rho_c^{4/3}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\frac{k_B T_c}{\mu m_p}=C_1 G M_c^{2/3}\rho_c^{1/3}$$
$$\rho_c^{1/3}
=\frac{k_B T_c}{C_1 G M_c^{2/3}\,\mu m_p}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\rho_c
=\Biggl(\frac{k_B T_c}{C_1 G M_c^{2/3}\,\mu m_p}\Biggr)^3\propto\mu^{-3}.$$
3. Ratio of final to initial density:
$$\frac{\rho_{c,f}}{\rho_{c,i}}
=\Bigl(\frac{\mu_i}{\mu_f}\Bigr)^3.$$
4. Mean molecular weights:
Initial (pure $^4$He, $Z=2,A=4$):
$$\mu_i^{-1}=\frac{1+2}{4}=\frac{3}{4},\quad\mu_i=\frac{4}{3}.$$
Final (50% $^{12}$C, 50% $^{16}$O):
$$\mu_f^{-1}
=\tfrac12\frac{1+6}{12}+\tfrac12\frac{1+8}{16}
=\frac{7}{24}+\frac{9}{32}
=\frac{55}{96},\quad\mu_f=\frac{96}{55}.$$
5. Therefore
$$\frac{\rho_{c,f}}{\rho_{c,i}}
=\Bigl(\frac{4/3}{96/55}\Bigr)^3
=\Bigl(\frac{55}{72}\Bigr)^3.$$
